==English==

===Etymology===
The name ''Prometheus'' literally means "forethought."

===Proper Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Prometheus'''

#{{greekmyth}}: The Titan chiefly honored for stealing fire from the gods in the stalk of a [fennel] plant and giving it to mortals for their use.  The god of fire and craft.  Prometheus had three brothers- [[Epimetheus]], [[Menoetios]] and [[Atlas]].

===Translations===

*Spanish: Prometeo